        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 4:31PM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 431 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles east of Theodore Roosevelt National Park North Unit, or 16
miles southeast of Watford City, moving southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Theodore Roosevelt National Park North Unit, Oakdale, and Little
Missouri State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
